#: ../../V/vadding.rst:5
msgid "vadding"
msgstr "vadding"

#: ../../V/vadding.rst:7
msgid "/vad´ing/, n\\."
msgstr "/vad´ing/, 名詞"

#: ../../V/vadding.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from VAD, a permutation of ADV (i.e., :ref:`ADVENT`\\), used to avoid a "
"particular :ref:`admin`\\'s continual search-and-destroy sweeps for the "
"game] A leisure-time activity of certain hackers involving the covert "
"exploration of the ‘secret’ parts of large buildings — basements, roofs, "
"freight elevators, maintenance crawlways, steam tunnels, and the like. A few"
" go so far as to learn locksmithing in order to synthesize vadding keys. The"
" verb is to vad (compare :ref:`phreaking`\\; see also :ref:`hack`\\, sense "
"9). This term dates from the late 1970s, before which such activity was "
"simply called ‘hacking’; the older usage is still prevalent at MIT."
msgstr ""
"[VADより。これはADV(すなわち\\ :ref:`ADVENT`\\ )の並べ替えで、特定の\\ :ref:`admin`\\ "
"がこのゲームを絶え間なく捜索・破壊して回るのを避けるために使われた] "
"一部のハッカーの余暇活動で、大きな建物の‘秘密の’部分——地下室、屋根、貨物用エレベータ、保守用の這い進む通路、蒸気トンネルなど——をひそかに探索するもの。一部の者はvadding用の鍵を作るために錠前作りを習うほどである。動詞はto"
" vad(\\ :ref:`phreaking`\\ と比較せよ。\\ :ref:`hack`\\ "
"の語義9も参照)。この用語は1970年代後半にさかのぼり、それ以前はこうした活動は単に‘hacking’と呼ばれていた。古い用法はMITでは今なお普及している。"

#: ../../V/vadding.rst:14
msgid ""
"The most extreme and dangerous form of vadding is elevator rodeo, a.k.a. "
"elevator surfing, a sport played by wrasslin' down a thousand-pound elevator"
" car with a 3-foot piece of string, and then exploiting this mastery in "
"various stimulating ways (such as elevator hopping, shaft exploration, rat-"
"racing, and the ever-popular drop experiments). Kids, don't try this at "
"home!"
msgstr ""
"vaddingのもっとも極端で危険な形態はelevator rodeo、別名elevator "
"surfingである。これは1000ポンドのエレベータの箱を3フィートの紐で組み伏せ、そののちこの熟達をさまざまな刺激的なやり方(elevator "
"hopping、シャフト探索、rat-"
"racing、そして永遠の人気を誇るdrop実験など)で活用する競技である。子供たちよ、家でこれを試してはいけない!"
